# FastAPI standards — {{WORKSPACE_NAME}}

> **Purpose**: The authoritative engineering-conventions document for every FastAPI (Python) repo in this workspace. Naming, auth, persistence, migrations, tests, app structure — **how we write FastAPI here**, not architecture (that's `platform.md`).
> **Last Updated**: {{DATE}}
> **Bootstrapped by**: PipeCrew `/discover` — Phase B2.5.

This document is populated by reading the actual code in the workspace's FastAPI repos. Every convention below names what already exists — not what the plugin thinks FastAPI "should" do. A repo on Tortoise ORM doesn't get SQLAlchemy rules; an app on Poetry doesn't get pip-tools advice.

**Stable section anchors (§1–§9) are cited by number from implementer and reviewer agents.** Do not renumber existing sections; you may add §10+.

