## §5 App layout & routers

**App structure**: {{APP_STRUCTURE}}

<!-- e.g.:
- One APIRouter per domain (users, books, contracts, ...) mounted under /api/v1
- Routers live in app/{feature}/routes.py; services in app/{feature}/services.py; models in app/{feature}/models.py
- Main app in app/main.py instantiates FastAPI, includes routers, registers middleware
-->

**Router registration**: {{ROUTER_REGISTRATION}}

<!-- app.include_router(users_router, prefix="/users", tags=["users"]) -->

**Rules:**
- {{APP_RULES}}

<!-- Example:
- Every new feature creates a new APIRouter; main.py's `include_router` list is the registry.
- Prefix + tags are set at include time, not in the router file — makes multi-version routing (v1/v2) possible.
- A router without middleware, error handlers, or event hooks lives in its own file; no magic at module import time.
-->

**Reference files:**
{{APP_REFERENCES}}

