## §6 Pydantic & error handling

**Pydantic version**: {{PYDANTIC_VERSION}}

<!-- v2 is dominant; v1 is legacy. V2 differs significantly (ConfigDict, model_validator, field_validator). Flag the version to avoid confusion. -->

**Schema style**: {{SCHEMA_STYLE}}

<!-- e.g.:
- Three schemas per resource: {Resource}Base (shared), {Resource}Create (POST), {Resource}Read (response)
- model_config = ConfigDict(from_attributes=True) for ORM conversion
- Field() for validation constraints; model_validator for cross-field rules
-->

**Global exception handlers**: {{ERROR_HANDLERS}}

<!-- @app.exception_handler(CustomException) mapped to JSON envelope; one handler per exception category -->

**Rules:**
- {{ERROR_RULES}}

<!-- Example:
- Never raise HTTPException from a service — raise a domain-specific exception (UserNotFoundError) and let the global handler map it.
- Response envelope for errors is consistent across the app: {error: {code, message, details}}.
- 404s come from a shared NotFoundError base, not ad-hoc HTTPException(404) calls.
-->

**Reference files:**
{{ERROR_REFERENCES}}

