## §7 Tests

**Test framework**: {{TEST_FRAMEWORK}}

<!-- pytest + pytest-asyncio (for async), TestClient or AsyncClient from httpx -->

**Fixture style**: {{FIXTURE_STYLE}}

<!-- e.g.:
- conftest.py at the package root provides app, client, db_session, authenticated_client fixtures
- DB setup: testcontainers / in-memory SQLite / dedicated test DB per CI run
-->

**Security test pattern** (if auth is enforced): {{SECURITY_TEST_PATTERN}}

<!-- e.g.:
- dependency_overrides[get_current_user] = lambda: MockUser(roles=[...])
- Or: JWT fixture that generates valid tokens for each role
- "Not established yet" — first feature adding auth establishes it
-->

**Rules:**
- {{TEST_RULES}}

<!-- Example:
- Every new route has an endpoint test (via TestClient) + a service-layer test (via pytest fixtures).
- Security tests use dependency_overrides to inject mock users; don't mock JWT decoding.
- Mock data in tests matches the production wire shape (no "simplified" shortcuts).
-->

**Reference files:**
{{TEST_REFERENCES}}

